definition.value: An amino cyclitol glycoside that is isolated from Streptomyces kasugaensis and exhibits antibiotic and fungicidal properties.
A chlorophyllide obtained by hydrolysis of the terpenoid ester moiety of 3-(1-hydroxyethyl)bacteriochlorophyll a.
A chlorophyllide obtained by hydrolysis of the terpenoid ester moiety of 3-(1-hydroxyethyl)chlorophyll a.
A chlorophyllide obtained by hydrolysis of the terpenoid ester moiety of bacteriochlorophyll a.
A chlorophyllide obtained by hydrolysis of the terpenoid ester moiety of 3-vinylbacteriochlorophyll d.
A chlorophyllide obtained by hydrolysis of the terpenoid ester moiety of any bacteriochlorophyll d.
A chlorophyllide obtained by hydrolysis of the terpenoid ester moiety of any bacteriochlorophyll c.

A dithiocarbamate salt resulting from the formal reaction of ethylenebis(dithiocarbamic acid) with 2 mol eq. of ammonia. A water-soluble crystalline solid, it is a fungicide used to protect fruit, vegetable, and field crops against a wide spectrum of fungal diseases. Mixing amobam with zinc sulfate affords the fungicide zineb.

A member of the class of bromoindoles that is 3-bromo-6-fluoro-2-methylindole substituted at position 1 by a 1-(dimethylsulfamyl)-1,2,4-triazole-3-sulfonyl group. A fungicide for use on potatoes to control late blight (Phytophthora infestans) and downy mildew [Plasmopara viticola). It has a low mammalian toxicity but it is considered to be a reproduction toxicant, is moderately toxic to birds and honey bees but poses a greater risk to aquatic species and earthworms.
A potassium salt that is the monopotassium salt of carbonic acid. It has fungicidal properties and is used in organic farming for the control of powdery mildew and apple scab.
The all-trans-isomer of phytoene.
A penicillin in which the substituent at position 6 of the penam ring is a 2-[(4-ethyl-2,3-dioxopiperazin-1-yl)carboxamido]-2-phenylacetamido group.
A polyazaalkane that is azacyclopentadecane in which the amino proton is replaced by a 3-(3-aminopropylamino)propyl group.
A spirostanyl glycoside that is isolated from Ophiopogon japonicus and exhibits antioxidant properties.
An elemental molecular entity in which all of the atoms have atomic number 26.
Any unsaturated fatty acid anion with one double or triple bond in the fatty acid chain.
A L-histidine derivative that is N(alpha),N(alpha),N(alpha)-trimethyl-L-histidine in which the hydrogen at position 2 on the imdazole ring is replaced by a thioxo group.
A member of the family of microcins comprising a heptapeptide covalently liinked to 3-aminopropyl-AMP via an acylphosphoramide linkage. A potent inhibitor of aspartyl-tRNA synthetase.
A 1-acyl-2-arachidonoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate(2-) in which the 1-acyl substituent is specified as heptadecanoyl

A subclass of opines, which are low molecular weight compounds found in plant crown gall tumours or hairy root tumours produced by parasitic bacteria of the genus Agrobacterium. Agrocinopines are set of sugar phosphodiester opines known to induce transfer of another Ti plasmid, pTiBo542.

A large family of low molecular weight compounds most commonly found in plant crown gall tumours or hairy root tumours produced by parasitic bacteria of the genus Agrobacterium. They are also found in marine invertebrates, fungi, higher plants and mammals.
A member of the class of agrocinopines that consists of two D-glucose units joined via a (2<->2)-phosphodiester linkage.
A family of sphingolipids that share a common structural feature, a sphinganine base backbone.
The pyranose form of D-lyxose.
A sphingomyelin in which the sphingoid component is specified as tetradecasphinganine.
A sphingomyelin in which the sphingoid component is specified as tetradecasphingosine.
A sphingomyelin in which the sphingoid component is specified as tetradecaphytosphingosine.
A sphingomyelin in which the sphingoid component is specified as hexadecasphinganine.
A sphingomyelin in which the sphingoid component is specified as hexadecasphingosine.
A sphingomyelin in which the sphingoid component is specified as hexadecaphytosphingosine.
A sphingomyelin in which the sphingoid component is specified as 15-methylhexadecasphinganine.
A sphingomyelin in which the sphingoid component is specified as icosasphinganine.
